 CellID->515410695,ExpressionUUID->"c79cfb92-f6bf-42a8-9a0b-bba3f5b070dd"],

Cell["\<\
As the number of qubits increases, it takes longer and longer to calculate \
the Gottesman matrices of given Clifford operators. It turns out that for \
some Clifford operators, it is faster to directly convert the operator \
expression, but sometimes, it is faster to first convert the operator \
expression to the matrix representation and then the matrix to the Gottesman \
matrix. Here, we take some examples in both cases.\
\>", "ExampleText",
 CellID->16870871,ExpressionUUID->"65760980-68be-4311-b08f-d5b17240fd4d"],

